Analyses - paper FunctionalLands

by Bruno X. Pinho

First, it is important to emphasize that the between region variance of the FC_scale variables is 31%, while the within-region variance is 69%. There is thus considerable within-region variation, the effect of which can be studied. Also, there is not much climate variation within regions (less then 3.5%), and the between regions effect of climate has been previously assessed.

data_LCD <- filter(data_lands, Region=="LCD")
WD_FC_LCD <- multifit(mod = "lm", multief = colnames(data_LCD)[19:26],
                      formula = WD ~ multief,
                      data = data_LCD, criterion = "R2", plot_est = T)
## The model including the effect 'FC_50ha' was the best model according to the specified criterion (R2, which.max)

Plot scales of effect by trait/region (filled points denote significant relationships at the specified scale)

ggplot(data=results_SE_all, aes(x = multief, y = R2, color = Region, group=Region))+
  geom_point(data=filter(results_SE_all, p.values > 0.05), shape=1, size=2)+
  geom_point(data=filter(results_SE_all, p.values <= 0.05), size=2)+
  geom_line(aes(multief, R2))+theme_bw()+
  theme(plot.background = element_blank(),panel.grid.major = element_blank(),panel.grid.minor = element_blank())+
  facet_grid( ~ response)
